
Download Dataset API and workflow:
-----------------------------------

1) Create a dataset file with following fields: 

Format JSON/TEXT ??

S.NO.   Name            URLs                                                                         License
1       Fountain        https://storage.googleapis.com/isl-datasets/open3d-dev/fountain.zip             MIT


E.g.

{"Fountain" : { 
      "url": [
          "https://storage.googleapis.com/isl-datasets/open3d-dev/fountain.zip"
      ]
      "license": "license_url"
      "tags": "tag1", "tag2",
      "HASH": ["
      "]},
 "Redwood-Objects" : {
      "url" : [
          "https://github.com/intel-isl/open3d_downloads/releases/download/Redwood-objects/chair.zip",
          "https://github.com/intel-isl/open3d_downloads/releases/download/Redwood-objects/car.zip" ]
      "license": "ODC-BY"}
 }


2) A cpp DatasetDownloadManager to download the dataset.

Usage: ./downloadDataset --name fountain --destination <path/to/folder>


Go through dataset url list:
print urls
print I have read the licence information for the {dataset}

User Input: Yes/No
No -> end
Yes,

Dataset is download and if it’s a zip or tar we extract its contents.
We copy the dataset to the DestinationFolder and delete the original.



Usage In examples
———————————————

If the user runs an example without any input, default dataset will be downloaded using the script and used for the example.

Example starts with print:

“Usage: ./run_example  [—-dataset /path/to/dataset/folder]

Using data from path: {defaultDatasetFolder/ inputDatsetFolder}

You may download and use other datasets listed in “DatasetList.json”


